arch Alliance projects in socially and economically marginalized communities. Bringing together experienced researchers with new scholars and community practitioners, the stories describe the impetus for the research projects, how they came to be implemented, and how CBPR is still being used to effect change within the community. The projects, ranging from engagement in public policy advocacy to learning from Elders in First Nations communities, were selected to demonstrate the breadth of experiences of those involved and the many different methods used. By providing space for researchers and their collaborators to share the stories behind their research, this book offers valuable lessons and rich insights into the power and practice of CBPR.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCommunitiesxResearchzManitobavCase studies. 0aParticipant observationzManitobavCase studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Research.2bisacsh1 aBarchyn, Maureen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrownlee, Clark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCooper, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFriesen, Claire, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarcia, Rosa Evelia Sanchez, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoodman, Janice, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHenry, Cheyenne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHill, Josie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlyne, Darlene, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLoxley, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMacKinnon, Shauna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary